: int) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def maximizeSum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        # Find the maximum element in the array\n        max_num = max(nums)\n        \n        # The maximum score can be achieved by always picking the maximum number\n        # and incrementing it for the next pick.\n        # The sum of the sequence will be max_num + (max_num + 1) + ... + (max_num + k - 1)\n        # This is an arithmetic series with the first term max_num, last term max_num + k - 1, and k terms.\n        # The sum of an arithmetic series is given by (number of terms) * (first term + last term) / 2\n        max_score = k * (max_num + max_num + k - 1) // 2\n        \n        return max_score\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the maximum score by leveraging the properties of arithmetic series. It always picks the maximum number available, increments it, and repeats this process exactly `k` times. The sum of the resulting sequence is computed using the formula for the sum of an arithmetic series.", "estimated_date": 1682208000000}